{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":985,"text":"I am a writer."},{"time":2552,"text":"Writing books is my profession\nbut it's more than that, of course."},{"time":6312,"text":"It is also my great lifelong\nlove and fascination."},{"time":10236,"text":"And I don't expect\nthat that's ever going to change."},{"time":13151,"text":"But, that said, something\nkind of peculiar has happened recently"},{"time":18186,"text":"in my life and in my career,"},{"time":20435,"text":"which has caused me to have to recalibrate\nmy whole relationship with this work."},{"time":25202,"text":"And the peculiar thing\nis that I recently wrote this book,"},{"time":28836,"text":"this memoir called \"Eat, Pray, Love\""},{"time":30804,"text":"which, decidedly\nunlike any of my previous books,"},{"time":35369,"text":"went out in the world\nfor some reason, and became this big,"},{"time":38437,"text":"mega-sensation, international\nbestseller thing."},{"time":41803,"text":"The result of which\nis that everywhere I go now,"},{"time":44869,"text":"people treat me like I'm doomed."},{"time":47469,"text":"Seriously -- doomed, doomed!"},{"time":50351,"text":"Like, they come up to me now,\nall worried, and they say,"},{"time":53042,"text":"\"Aren't you afraid you're never\ngoing to be able to top that?"},{"time":57240,"text":"Aren't you afraid you're going\nto keep writing for your whole life"},{"time":60486,"text":"and you're never again\ngoing to create a book"},{"time":62653,"text":"that anybody in the world\ncares about at all,"},{"time":65219,"text":"ever again?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":67719,"text":"So that's reassuring, you know."},{"time":70068,"text":"But it would be worse,\nexcept for that I happen to remember"},{"time":72879,"text":"that over 20 years ago,\nwhen I was a teenager,"},{"time":76138,"text":"when I first started telling people\nthat I wanted to be a writer,"},{"time":79285,"text":"I was met with this same\nsort of fear-based reaction."},{"time":81856,"text":"And people would say, \"Aren't you afraid\nyou're never going to have any success?"},{"time":85690,"text":"Aren't you afraid the humiliation\nof rejection will kill you?"},{"time":88637,"text":"Aren't you afraid that you're going\nto work your whole life at this craft"},{"time":92121,"text":"and nothing's ever going to come of it"},{"time":94001,"text":"and you're going to die\non a scrap heap of broken dreams"},{"time":96660,"text":"with your mouth filled\nwith bitter ash of failure?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":99151,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":100504,"text":"Like that, you know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":102356,"text":"The answer -- the short answer\nto all those questions is, \"Yes.\""},{"time":107517,"text":"Yes, I'm afraid of all those things."},{"time":109817,"text":"And I always have been."},{"time":111082,"text":"And I'm afraid of many,\nmany more things besides"},{"time":113392,"text":"that people can't even guess at,"},{"time":115317,"text":"like seaweed and other\nthings that are scary."},{"time":119298,"text":"But, when it comes to writing,"},{"time":121549,"text":"the thing that I've been sort of thinking\nabout lately, and wondering about lately,"},{"time":125533,"text":"is why?"},{"time":126707,"text":"You know, is it rational?"},{"time":128001,"text":"Is it logical that anybody\nshould be expected"},{"time":130248,"text":"to be afraid of the work that they feel\nthey were put on this Earth to do."},{"time":134900,"text":"And what is it specifically\nabout creative ventures"},{"time":139300,"text":"that seems to make us really nervous\nabout each other's mental health"},{"time":142772,"text":"in a way that other careers\nkind of don't do, you know?"},{"time":145799,"text":"Like my dad, for example,\nwas a chemical engineer"},{"time":149822,"text":"and I don't recall once in his 40 years\nof chemical engineering"},{"time":153199,"text":"anybody asking him if he was afraid\nto be a chemical engineer, you know?"},{"time":156881,"text":"\"That chemical-engineering block,\nJohn, how's it going?\""},{"time":162692,"text":"It just didn't come up\nlike that, you know?"},{"time":164856,"text":"But to be fair,\nchemical engineers as a group"},{"time":168690,"text":"haven't really earned\na reputation over the centuries"},{"time":171238,"text":"for being alcoholic manic-depressives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":173934,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":175382,"text":"We writers, we kind of do have\nthat reputation,"},{"time":178216,"text":"and not just writers,\nbut creative people across all genres,"},{"time":182199,"text":"it seems, have this reputation\nfor being enormously mentally unstable."},{"time":186900,"text":"And all you have to do is look\nat the very grim death count"},{"time":190716,"text":"in the 20th century alone,\nof really magnificent creative minds"},{"time":194299,"text":"who died young and often\nat their own hands, you know?"},{"time":197425,"text":"And even the ones\nwho didn't literally commit suicide"},{"time":200691,"text":"seem to be really undone\nby their gifts, you know."},{"time":204067,"text":"Norman Mailer, just before he died,\nlast interview, he said,"},{"time":206966,"text":"\"Every one of my books\nhas killed me a little more.\""},{"time":211067,"text":"An extraordinary statement\nto make about your life's work."},{"time":214666,"text":"But we don't even blink\nwhen we hear somebody say this,"},{"time":217626,"text":"because we've heard\nthat kind of stuff for so long"},{"time":220232,"text":"and somehow we've completely\ninternalized and accepted collectively"},{"time":224233,"text":"this notion that creativity and suffering\nare somehow inherently linked"},{"time":228900,"text":"and that artistry, in the end,\nwill always ultimately lead to anguish."}]},{"cues":[{"time":233966,"text":"And the question that I want\nto ask everybody here today"},{"time":236657,"text":"is are you guys all cool with that idea?"},{"time":239174,"text":"Are you comfortable with that?"},{"time":241381,"text":"Because you look at it\neven from an inch away and, you know --"},{"time":244405,"text":"I'm not at all comfortable\nwith that assumption."},{"time":247532,"text":"I think it's odious."},{"time":249018,"text":"And I also think it's dangerous,"},{"time":250971,"text":"and I don't want to see it\nperpetuated into the next century."},{"time":253900,"text":"I think it's better if we encourage\nour great creative minds to live."}]},{"cues":[{"time":257774,"text":"And I definitely know that,\nin my case -- in my situation --"},{"time":263549,"text":"it would be very dangerous for me to start\nsort of leaking down that dark path"},{"time":268712,"text":"of assumption,"},{"time":269933,"text":"particularly given the circumstance\nthat I'm in right now in my career."},{"time":274086,"text":"Which is -- you know, like check it out,"},{"time":276625,"text":"I'm pretty young,\nI'm only about 40 years old."},{"time":278840,"text":"I still have maybe another four\ndecades of work left in me."},{"time":282134,"text":"And it's exceedingly likely that anything\nI write from this point forward"},{"time":286651,"text":"is going to be judged by the world\nas the work that came after"},{"time":289628,"text":"the freakish success\nof my last book, right?"},{"time":292951,"text":"I should just put it bluntly, because\nwe're all sort of friends here now --"},{"time":296913,"text":"it's exceedingly likely\nthat my greatest success is behind me."},{"time":301194,"text":"So Jesus, what a thought!"},{"time":303394,"text":"That's the kind of thought\nthat could lead a person"},{"time":305824,"text":"to start drinking gin\nat nine o'clock in the morning,"},{"time":308452,"text":"and I don't want to go there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":311389,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":312447,"text":"I would prefer to keep doing\nthis work that I love."}]},{"cues":[{"time":314901,"text":"And so, the question becomes, how?"},{"time":318239,"text":"And so, it seems to me,\nupon a lot of reflection,"},{"time":321123,"text":"that the way that I have to work now,\nin order to continue writing,"},{"time":324488,"text":"is that I have to create some sort of\nprotective psychological construct, right?"},{"time":328322,"text":"I have to sort of find some way\nto have a safe distance"},{"time":331822,"text":"between me, as I am writing,\nand my very natural anxiety"},{"time":336707,"text":"about what the reaction to that writing\nis going to be, from now on."},{"time":340572,"text":"And, as I've been looking,\nover the last year,"},{"time":342983,"text":"for models for how to do that,"},{"time":344840,"text":"I've been sort of looking across time,"},{"time":346988,"text":"and I've been trying\nto find other societies"},{"time":349090,"text":"to see if they might have had\nbetter and saner ideas than we have"},{"time":352840,"text":"about how to help creative people"},{"time":355067,"text":"sort of manage the inherent\nemotional risks of creativity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358873,"text":"And that search has led me\nto ancient Greece and ancient Rome."},{"time":363888,"text":"So stay with me, because\nit does circle around and back."},{"time":366579,"text":"But, ancient Greece and ancient Rome --"},{"time":368735,"text":"people did not happen\nto believe that creativity"},{"time":371301,"text":"came from human beings back then, OK?"},{"time":373719,"text":"People believed that creativity\nwas this divine attendant spirit"},{"time":378178,"text":"that came to human beings\nfrom some distant and unknowable source,"},{"time":382179,"text":"for distant and unknowable reasons."},{"time":384628,"text":"The Greeks famously called these divine\nattendant spirits of creativity \"daemons.\""},{"time":389879,"text":"Socrates, famously, believed\nthat he had a daemon"},{"time":392979,"text":"who spoke wisdom to him from afar."}]},{"cues":[{"time":395436,"text":"The Romans had the same idea,"},{"time":397053,"text":"but they called that sort of disembodied\ncreative spirit a genius."},{"time":401663,"text":"Which is great, because the Romans\ndid not actually think"},{"time":404402,"text":"that a genius was a particularly\nclever individual."},{"time":407196,"text":"They believed that a genius was this,\nsort of magical divine entity,"},{"time":410879,"text":"who was believed to literally\nlive in the walls of an artist's studio,"},{"time":416201,"text":"kind of like Dobby the house elf,"},{"time":418745,"text":"and who would come out"},{"time":420283,"text":"and sort of invisibly assist\nthe artist with their work"},{"time":422909,"text":"and would shape the outcome of that work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":425378,"text":"So brilliant -- there it is, right there,\nthat distance that I'm talking about --"},{"time":429260,"text":"that psychological construct to protect\nyou from the results of your work."},{"time":433462,"text":"And everyone knew that this\nis how it functioned, right?"},{"time":437070,"text":"So the ancient artist was protected\nfrom certain things,"},{"time":439761,"text":"like, for example,\ntoo much narcissism, right?"},{"time":442162,"text":"If your work was brilliant,\nyou couldn't take all the credit for it,"},{"time":445377,"text":"everybody knew that you had this\ndisembodied genius who had helped you."},{"time":449096,"text":"If your work bombed,\nnot entirely your fault, you know?"},{"time":452465,"text":"Everyone knew your genius\nwas kind of lame."}]},{"cues":[{"time":454983,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":456041,"text":"And this is how people\nthought about creativity in the West"},{"time":459563,"text":"for a really long time."},{"time":460895,"text":"And then the Renaissance came\nand everything changed,"},{"time":463495,"text":"and we had this big idea,\nand the big idea was,"},{"time":465810,"text":"let's put the individual human being\nat the center of the universe"},{"time":469029,"text":"above all gods and mysteries,"},{"time":470594,"text":"and there's no more room\nfor mystical creatures"},{"time":472903,"text":"who take dictation from the divine."},{"time":474695,"text":"And it's the beginning\nof rational humanism,"},{"time":476830,"text":"and people started\nto believe that creativity"},{"time":478997,"text":"came completely from the self\nof the individual."},{"time":481361,"text":"And for the first time in history,"},{"time":483211,"text":"you start to hear people referring\nto this or that artist as being a genius,"},{"time":488322,"text":"rather than having a genius."}]},{"cues":[{"time":490163,"text":"And I got to tell you,\nI think that was a huge error."},{"time":493487,"text":"You know, I think that allowing\nsomebody, one mere person"},{"time":497733,"text":"to believe that he or she is like,\nthe vessel,"},{"time":500496,"text":"you know, like the font\nand the essence and the source"},{"time":503092,"text":"of all divine, creative,\nunknowable, eternal mystery"},{"time":506445,"text":"is just a smidge too much responsibility\nto put on one fragile, human psyche."},{"time":512530,"text":"It's like asking somebody\nto swallow the sun."},{"time":516045,"text":"It just completely warps\nand distorts egos,"},{"time":518696,"text":"and it creates all these unmanageable\nexpectations about performance."},{"time":522246,"text":"And I think the pressure of that"},{"time":524245,"text":"has been killing off our artists\nfor the last 500 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":527462,"text":"And, if this is true,"},{"time":530127,"text":"and I think it is true,"},{"time":531713,"text":"the question becomes, what now?"},{"time":534578,"text":"Can we do this differently?"},{"time":536447,"text":"Maybe go back to some more\nancient understanding"},{"time":539843,"text":"about the relationship between humans\nand the creative mystery."},{"time":544344,"text":"Maybe not."},{"time":545697,"text":"Maybe we can't just erase 500 years\nof rational humanistic thought"},{"time":549579,"text":"in one 18 minute speech."},{"time":551737,"text":"And there's probably\npeople in this audience"},{"time":554446,"text":"who would raise really\nlegitimate scientific suspicions"},{"time":558561,"text":"about the notion of, basically, fairies"},{"time":560940,"text":"who follow people around rubbing fairy\njuice on their projects and stuff."},{"time":565928,"text":"I'm not, probably, going to bring\nyou all along with me on this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":570245,"text":"But the question\nthat I kind of want to pose is --"},{"time":573030,"text":"you know, why not?"},{"time":575227,"text":"Why not think about it this way?"},{"time":577149,"text":"Because it makes as much sense\nas anything else I have ever heard"},{"time":581261,"text":"in terms of explaining\nthe utter maddening capriciousness"},{"time":585217,"text":"of the creative process."},{"time":586762,"text":"A process which, as anybody\nwho has ever tried to make something --"},{"time":589977,"text":"which is to say basically\neveryone here ---"},{"time":592067,"text":"knows does not always behave rationally."},{"time":595178,"text":"And, in fact, can sometimes\nfeel downright paranormal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":599761,"text":"I had this encounter recently"},{"time":601537,"text":"where I met the extraordinary\nAmerican poet Ruth Stone,"},{"time":605246,"text":"who's now in her 90s,\nbut she's been a poet her entire life"},{"time":608081,"text":"and she told me that when\nshe was growing up in rural Virginia,"},{"time":611311,"text":"she would be out working in the fields,"},{"time":613193,"text":"and she said she would feel\nand hear a poem"},{"time":616069,"text":"coming at her from over the landscape."},{"time":618076,"text":"And she said it was like\na thunderous train of air."},{"time":621233,"text":"And it would come barreling down\nat her over the landscape."},{"time":624061,"text":"And she felt it coming, because it\nwould shake the earth under her feet."},{"time":627563,"text":"She knew that she had\nonly one thing to do at that point,"},{"time":630362,"text":"and that was to,\nin her words, \"run like hell.\""},{"time":632613,"text":"And she would run like hell to the house"},{"time":634645,"text":"and she would be getting\nchased by this poem,"},{"time":636831,"text":"and the whole deal was that she had\nto get to a piece of paper and a pencil"},{"time":640461,"text":"fast enough so that when it thundered\nthrough her, she could collect it"},{"time":643866,"text":"and grab it on the page."},{"time":645072,"text":"And other times\nshe wouldn't be fast enough,"},{"time":647185,"text":"so she'd be running and running,\nand she wouldn't get to the house"},{"time":650412,"text":"and the poem would barrel\nthrough her and she would miss it"},{"time":653250,"text":"and she said it would continue\non across the landscape,"},{"time":655894,"text":"looking, as she put it \"for another poet.\""},{"time":658002,"text":"And then there were these times --"},{"time":659672,"text":"this is the piece I never forgot --"},{"time":661551,"text":"she said that there were moments\nwhere she would almost miss it, right?"},{"time":665033,"text":"So, she's running to the house\nand she's looking for the paper"},{"time":668084,"text":"and the poem passes through her,"},{"time":669701,"text":"and she grabs a pencil just\nas it's going through her,"},{"time":672335,"text":"and then she said, it was like\nshe would reach out with her other hand"},{"time":675703,"text":"and she would catch it."},{"time":677010,"text":"She would catch the poem by its tail,"},{"time":678991,"text":"and she would pull it\nbackwards into her body"},{"time":681569,"text":"as she was transcribing on the page."},{"time":683429,"text":"And in these instances, the poem would\ncome up on the page perfect and intact"},{"time":688284,"text":"but backwards, from the last\nword to the first."}]},{"cues":[{"time":691689,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":693401,"text":"So when I heard that I was like --\nthat's uncanny,"},{"time":698118,"text":"that's exactly what my creative\nprocess is like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":700619,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":704232,"text":"That's not at all what my creative\nprocess is -- I'm not the pipeline!"},{"time":707598,"text":"I'm a mule, and the way\nthat I have to work"},{"time":709652,"text":"is I have to get up\nat the same time every day,"},{"time":711919,"text":"and sweat and labor and barrel\nthrough it really awkwardly."},{"time":714753,"text":"But even I, in my mulishness,"},{"time":716616,"text":"even I have brushed\nup against that thing, at times."},{"time":720484,"text":"And I would imagine\nthat a lot of you have too."},{"time":722747,"text":"You know, even I have had work\nor ideas come through me from a source"},{"time":726052,"text":"that I honestly cannot identify."},{"time":728563,"text":"And what is that thing?"},{"time":730159,"text":"And how are we to relate to it in a way\nthat will not make us lose our minds,"},{"time":734197,"text":"but, in fact, might actually keep us sane?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":737083,"text":"And for me, the best contemporary\nexample that I have of how to do that"},{"time":740862,"text":"is the musician Tom Waits,"},{"time":743194,"text":"who I got to interview several years ago\non a magazine assignment."},{"time":747735,"text":"And we were talking about this,"},{"time":749236,"text":"and you know, Tom, for most of his life,\nhe was pretty much the embodiment"},{"time":752797,"text":"of the tormented\ncontemporary modern artist,"},{"time":754917,"text":"trying to control and manage and dominate"},{"time":757244,"text":"these sort of uncontrollable\ncreative impulses"},{"time":759718,"text":"that were totally internalized."}]},{"cues":[{"time":761605,"text":"But then he got older, he got calmer,"},{"time":763610,"text":"and one day he was driving down\nthe freeway in Los Angeles,"},{"time":766533,"text":"and this is when it all changed for him."},{"time":768469,"text":"And he's speeding along,\nand all of a sudden"},{"time":770559,"text":"he hears this little fragment of melody,"},{"time":774105,"text":"that comes into his head as inspiration\noften comes, elusive and tantalizing,"},{"time":778134,"text":"and he wants it, it's gorgeous,"},{"time":780262,"text":"and he longs for it,\nbut he has no way to get it."},{"time":782587,"text":"He doesn't have a piece of paper,\nor a pencil, or a tape recorder."}]},{"cues":[{"time":785762,"text":"So he starts to feel all of that old\nanxiety start to rise in him"},{"time":788846,"text":"like, \"I'm going to lose this thing,"},{"time":790611,"text":"and I'll be be haunted\nby this song forever."},{"time":792731,"text":"I'm not good enough, and I can't do it.\""},{"time":794660,"text":"And instead of panicking, he just stopped."},{"time":796694,"text":"He just stopped that whole mental process\nand he did something completely novel."},{"time":800836,"text":"He just looked up at the sky, and he said,"},{"time":803319,"text":"\"Excuse me, can you not\nsee that I'm driving?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":806333,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":810034,"text":"\"Do I look like I can write\ndown a song right now?"},{"time":812768,"text":"If you really want to exist,\ncome back at a more opportune moment"},{"time":816613,"text":"when I can take care of you."},{"time":818275,"text":"Otherwise, go bother somebody else today."},{"time":821352,"text":"Go bother Leonard Cohen.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":824648,"text":"And his whole work process\nchanged after that."},{"time":827780,"text":"Not the work, the work was still\noftentimes as dark as ever."},{"time":831388,"text":"But the process, and the heavy\nanxiety around it"},{"time":834447,"text":"was released when he took\nthe genie, the genius out of him"},{"time":837394,"text":"where it was causing nothing but trouble,\nand released it back where it came from,"},{"time":841305,"text":"and realized that this didn't have to be\nthis internalized, tormented thing."},{"time":844966,"text":"It could be this peculiar,\nwondrous, bizarre collaboration,"},{"time":848104,"text":"kind of conversation between\nTom and the strange, external thing"},{"time":852236,"text":"that was not quite Tom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":854469,"text":"When I heard that story,\nit started to shift a little bit"},{"time":857176,"text":"the way that I worked too,\nand this idea already saved me once."},{"time":860205,"text":"It saved me when I was in the middle\nof writing \"Eat, Pray, Love,\""},{"time":863333,"text":"and I fell into one of those\nsort of pits of despair"},{"time":865866,"text":"that we all fall into when we're working\non something and it's not coming"},{"time":869346,"text":"and you start to think this is going to be\na disaster, the worst book ever written."},{"time":873530,"text":"Not just bad, but the worst\nbook ever written."},{"time":875904,"text":"And I started to think I should\njust dump this project."},{"time":879319,"text":"But then I remembered Tom\ntalking to the open air"},{"time":882394,"text":"and I tried it."},{"time":884442,"text":"So I just lifted my face\nup from the manuscript"},{"time":886934,"text":"and I directed my comments\nto an empty corner of the room."},{"time":889864,"text":"And I said aloud, \"Listen you, thing,"},{"time":893442,"text":"you and I both know\nthat if this book isn't brilliant"},{"time":896640,"text":"that is not entirely my fault, right?"},{"time":898441,"text":"Because you can see that I am putting\neverything I have into this,"},{"time":901697,"text":"I don't have any more than this."},{"time":903336,"text":"If you want it to be better, you've got\nto show up and do your part of the deal."},{"time":907145,"text":"But if you don't do that,\nyou know what, the hell with it."},{"time":909986,"text":"I'm going to keep writing anyway\nbecause that's my job."},{"time":912692,"text":"And I would please\nlike the record to reflect today"},{"time":915152,"text":"that I showed up for my part of the job.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":917174,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":920189,"text":"Because --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":922276,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":924350,"text":"Because in the end it's like this, OK --"},{"time":926522,"text":"centuries ago in the deserts\nof North Africa,"},{"time":928923,"text":"people used to gather for these moonlight\ndances of sacred dance and music"},{"time":933590,"text":"that would go on for hours\nand hours, until dawn."},{"time":936294,"text":"They were always magnificent,\nbecause the dancers were professionals"},{"time":939538,"text":"and they were terrific, right?"},{"time":940992,"text":"But every once in a while, very rarely,\nsomething would happen,"},{"time":944313,"text":"and one of these performers\nwould actually become transcendent."},{"time":947825,"text":"And I know you know\nwhat I'm talking about,"},{"time":950109,"text":"because I know you've all seen,\nat some point in your life,"},{"time":952929,"text":"a performance like this."},{"time":954229,"text":"It was like time would stop,"},{"time":956158,"text":"and the dancer would sort of step\nthrough some kind of portal"},{"time":959087,"text":"and he wasn't doing anything different"},{"time":960991,"text":"than he had ever done,\n1,000 nights before,"},{"time":963024,"text":"but everything would align."},{"time":964775,"text":"And all of a sudden, he would\nno longer appear to be merely human."},{"time":967942,"text":"He would be lit from within,\nand lit from below"},{"time":970341,"text":"and all lit up on fire with divinity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":974131,"text":"And when this happened, back then,"},{"time":976276,"text":"people knew it for what it was,\nyou know, they called it by its name."},{"time":980492,"text":"They would put their hands together\nand they would start to chant,"},{"time":983659,"text":"\"Allah, Allah, Allah, God, God, God.\""},{"time":987224,"text":"That's God, you know."},{"time":990326,"text":"Curious historical footnote:"},{"time":993006,"text":"when the Moors invaded southern Spain,\nthey took this custom with them"},{"time":997847,"text":"and the pronunciation\nchanged over the centuries"},{"time":1000157,"text":"from \"Allah, Allah, Allah,\"\nto \"Olé, olé, olé,\""},{"time":1002957,"text":"which you still hear in bullfights\nand in flamenco dances."},{"time":1006131,"text":"In Spain, when a performer has done\nsomething impossible and magic,"},{"time":1009784,"text":"\"Allah, olé, olé, Allah,\nmagnificent, bravo,\""},{"time":1012933,"text":"incomprehensible, there it is\n-- a glimpse of God."},{"time":1016387,"text":"Which is great, because we need that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1018509,"text":"But, the tricky bit\ncomes the next morning,"},{"time":1022360,"text":"for the dancer himself,\nwhen he wakes up and discovers"},{"time":1025787,"text":"that it's Tuesday at 11 a.m.,\nand he's no longer a glimpse of God."},{"time":1029234,"text":"He's just an aging mortal\nwith really bad knees,"},{"time":1032726,"text":"and maybe he's never going\nto ascend to that height again."},{"time":1036966,"text":"And maybe nobody will ever chant\nGod's name again as he spins,"},{"time":1040693,"text":"and what is he then to do\nwith the rest of his life?"},{"time":1043551,"text":"This is hard."},{"time":1044933,"text":"This is one of the most painful\nreconciliations to make"},{"time":1047775,"text":"in a creative life."},{"time":1049866,"text":"But maybe it doesn't have to be\nquite so full of anguish"},{"time":1053049,"text":"if you never happened\nto believe, in the first place,"},{"time":1056316,"text":"that the most extraordinary aspects\nof your being came from you."},{"time":1060421,"text":"But maybe if you just believed\nthat they were on loan to you"},{"time":1063282,"text":"from some unimaginable source\nfor some exquisite portion of your life"},{"time":1066890,"text":"to be passed along when you're finished,"},{"time":1068930,"text":"with somebody else."},{"time":1070781,"text":"And, you know, if we think about it\nthis way, it starts to change everything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1075586,"text":"This is how I've started to think,"},{"time":1077450,"text":"and this is certainly how I've been\nthinking in the last few months"},{"time":1080799,"text":"as I've been working on the book\nthat will soon be published,"},{"time":1083728,"text":"as the dangerously, frighteningly\nover-anticipated follow up"},{"time":1087283,"text":"to my freakish success."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1089943,"text":"And what I have to\nsort of keep telling myself"},{"time":1092866,"text":"when I get really psyched out\nabout that is don't be afraid."},{"time":1097066,"text":"Don't be daunted. Just do your job."},{"time":1100415,"text":"Continue to show up for your piece of it,\nwhatever that might be."},{"time":1103535,"text":"If your job is to dance, do your dance."},{"time":1106300,"text":"If the divine, cockeyed genius\nassigned to your case"},{"time":1110265,"text":"decides to let some sort of wonderment\nbe glimpsed, for just one moment"},{"time":1115349,"text":"through your efforts, then \"Olé!\""},{"time":1118053,"text":"And if not, do your dance anyhow."},{"time":1120988,"text":"And \"Olé!\" to you, nonetheless."},{"time":1122669,"text":"I believe this and I feel\nthat we must teach it."},{"time":1124979,"text":"\"Olé!\" to you, nonetheless,"},{"time":1126457,"text":"just for having the sheer\nhuman love and stubbornness"},{"time":1129770,"text":"to keep showing up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1131615,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1133290,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1135365,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1136856,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1139970,"text":"June Cohen: Olé!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1141803,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}